AdV-positive episodes tended to protect against subsequent infection with AdV (
 P = .090) and also 3 other virus groups commonly encountered in BMT, namely CoV, ERV, and FluV (
 P = .062, .093, and .064 respectively; 
 Supplementary Figure 2). FluV–positive FRI episodes significantly reduced the risk of subsequent AdV infection (
 P = .044; 
 Supplementary Figure 3
  A
 ). Cross-protection between FluV episodes was not apparent in the full data set (
 Supplementary Figure 3
  B
 ). However, before routine administration of TIV (ie, on or before 4 October 2010), FluV–positive episodes tended to protect against subsequent FluV infection in enlistees who had not recently received TIV (
 P = .081; 
 Supplementary Figure 3
  C
 ). None of the other virus groups conferred significant group-specific protection (
 Supplementary Table 3).
